<H3> <TI>   MONTSAME Carries 15 Mar Press Review </TI></H3>
<F P=102>  OW1503174394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1617 GMT 15 Mar 
94 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW1503174394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>


<TEXT>
Language: <F P=105> English </F>
Article Type:BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, March 15 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
newspaper "ARDIYN ERH" informs that the Prime Minister P. Jasrat 
has visited departments of police of some districts of the 
Mongolian capital, get acquainted with work of policemen. As 
the newspaper notes, the prime minister has paid attention to 
the growth of cases of stealing and hard-drinking in the city. 
The police organs have noted that a striving for "an easy life" 
furthers the increase of cases of stealing. Cases of stealing 
are often committed by persons in a drunken state. Lately cases 
of cattle stealing have become very frequent. As the newspaper 
informs, the prime minister has decided to meet tomorrow with 
the personnel of the central police department to discuss 
problems of struggle with criminality. 
  "ARDIYN ERH" publishes a number of materials about electric 
energy and heat supply. The directors of the thermo-electric 
power stations of Ulaanbaatar and the chief of the control 
service of the central electric energy system note that more 
than 50 percent of damages at the electric power stations have 
been in consequence of irresponsible work and bad discipline of 
workers, low qualification level of workers and 
engineering-technical personnel and weak control. The newspaper 
notes that to maintain normal work at the two biggest 
thermo-electric power stations of the city, a special strict 
regime is introduced there for the period of half a month. 
  The newspaper informs about the joint meeting of the State 
Great Hural Standing Committees on Food and Agriculture, on 
Budget-Finance and Currency Credit Policy and on Policy of 
Development of Economy and Infrastructure. At the sitting, 
information of the Minister of Food and Agriculture T. Oold was 
heard about a conception of development of agriculture and 
preparation for the spring sowing. In the report it is noted 
that in the current year it is envisaged to sow more than 553 
thousand hectares with food grains, 9, 6 thousand hectares with 
potatoes, 3, 4 thousand hectares with vegetables, about 40 
thousand hectares with fodder crops. At the sitting it was 
pointed out to unsatisfactory preparation of agricultural 
machines for the spring sowing, and it was noted that the plan 
of repair of machines is fulfilled for the present only by 20 
percent. 
  At the sitting the President of Mongol Bank D. Molomjamts 
announced that the bank has granted additional credits for 
carrying out the spring field works, but the bank was not able 
to grant them on favourable terms. 
  "ARDIYN ERH" publishes an article "The Last Night of Pompei" 
by the State Great Hural (SGH) member from the opposition T. 
Elbegdorj. He notes that a crisis is observed in the parliament 
of Mongolia in consequence of an unequal balance of different 
political forces in the State Great Hural. 
  In the article it is noted that the government still fails 
to 
realize its program, has not met its engagements to meet the 
requirements of the population in food in 1993. Pointing out to 
insufficient steps in the sphere of democratization of the 
society and transition of economy to market relations, T. 
Elbegdorj considers that the present situation in the country 
reminds [is similar to] Pompei before the explosion of the 
volcano Vesuvius at the beginning of our era. 
  The newspaper of the Mongolian capital "ULAANBAATAR" informs 
about the exhibitions under the motto "Each Family Enterprise, 
Each Citizen-Producer". Such exhibitions are organized lately 
regularly at the halls of the former museum of V. I. Lenin. The 
newspaper notes that many districts of the city, hundreds of 
citizens are successfully engaged in production activity. They 
are producing different goods and food-products. The newspaper 
notes that this kind of work is especially widely spreading in 
the Chingeltei District of Ulaanbaatar, number of horoos 
(horoo-territorial administrative primary unit) of which was 
granted a premium for their success in production activity. 
  The head of the sector of the Epidemiological Center L. 
Togooch in an interview with the newspaper correspondent 
announces that among the city population, particularly among 
children cases of falling ill with infectious meningitis are 
still observed. L. Togooch notes that an external factor of 
spreading of meningitis is cold weather. As he says, in all 
probability the falling ill with meningitis will not stop till 
June. At present in the city two teams of physicians are 
working on liquidation of hotbeds of this disease. 
  The newspaper publishes materials devoted to the 
international day of consumers, in particular, publishes the 
statement of the society of protection of consumer's interests 
of the capital, an information about the international union of 
consumers. 

